{"name":"fsweb","version":"0.8.6","description":"static http web server with live reload.","main":"./src/index.js","scripts":{"test":"node test/index.js"},"bin":{"fsweb":"./fsweb"},"preferGlobal":true,"keywords":["restart","watch","live reload"],"repository":"https://github.com/sinclairzx81/fsweb-ts","license":"MIT","homepage":"https://github.com/sinclairzx81/fsweb-ts#readme","versions":[{"number":"0.8.0","date":"2016-09-22T13:31:36.979Z"},{"number":"0.8.1","date":"2016-09-22T13:34:28.595Z"},{"number":"0.8.2","date":"2016-09-23T07:17:55.014Z"},{"number":"0.8.3","date":"2016-09-23T07:59:33.065Z"},{"number":"0.8.4","date":"2016-09-27T12:04:19.988Z"},{"number":"0.8.5","date":"2016-10-25T09:54:46.404Z"},{"number":"0.8.6","date":"2017-05-10T01:13:29.244Z"}],"readme":"# fsweb\n\nstatic http server with live reload on save.\n\n```\n> fsweb ./ 5000\n```\n## install\n```\nnpm install fsweb -g\n```\n\n## overview\n\nfsweb is a simple command line utility to quickly serve static content over http and\nprovides automatic live reload functionality whenever content in the directory changes.\n\nfsweb has been tested in internet explorer, firefox, chrome, opera and edge browsers.\n\n## starting the server\n\nIf not stated otherwise, fsweb will serve content from the current working directory on port 5000\n\n```\n> fsweb\n```\n\nUsers can override the path and the port as follows.\n\n```\n> fsweb ./directory_to_watch 8080\n```\nwhich will serve/watch this directory and listen on port 8080. \n\nAlternatively\n```\n> fsweb 8080\n```\nwill watch the current working directory on port 8080.\n\n\n\n\n","created":"2016-09-22T13:31:36.979Z","modified":"2017-05-10T01:13:29.244Z","lastPublisher":{"name":"sinclair","email":"haydn.developer@gmail.com"},"owners":[{"name":"sinclair","email":"haydn.developer@gmail.com"}],"other":{"_attachments":{},"_from":".","_id":"fsweb","_nodeVersion":"7.9.0","_npmOperationalInternal":{"host":"packages-12-west.internal.npmjs.com","tmp":"tmp/fsweb-0.8.6.tgz_1494